a. Displaying the first 10 lines of the file:

bash

head lsoutput

b. Displaying the file starting from the 10th line:

bash

tail +10 lsoutput

For scrolling up and down, you can use commands like less, more, or vim.

i. Scrolling Up:

bash

less lsoutput

Then you can press the Up arrow key to scroll up.

ii. Scrolling Up and Down:

bash

vim lsoutput

